article.headline: Maine 76, Quinnipiac 71
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- Justin Edwards scored 26 points and Alasdair Fraser had 14 points and 11 rebounds as Maine beat Quinnipiac 76-71 Saturday. Jon Mesghna added 13 points for Maine (5-8). Ahead 48-44 with 17 minutes to play, Mesghna's 3-pointer and Edwards' layup gave Maine its biggest lead of the half, 53-44, with 16:22 remaining. Quinnipiac (4-7) answered with a 15-6 run to tie the game at 59 with 9:48 left to play. The teams traded baskets over the final 10 minutes but Edwards scored nine points during the span to give the Black Bears a 74-69 advantage with 1:17 remaining. Evan Conti made a layup to cut Quinnipiac's deficit to three, 74-71 with 47 seconds left to play, but Zaid Heart missed a tying 3-pointer and Fraser hit two free throws for Maine with 5 seconds left to seal the victory. Ike Azotam finished with 16 points and nine rebounds for Quinnipiac.
